This paper proposes a distributed matrix decomposition model for big data analytics, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The paper discusses the use of accelerated gradient descent, ADMM, and statistical inference to implement distributed computing, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian methods, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of matrix decomposition for clustering, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of statistical inference to address heterogeneity in the data, which falls under the category of statistical inference (cs.SI). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
